human_feedback:
make sure these parameters are evalulated:
Eval 1: Framework Integrity (Atomic Split)

We split framework evaluation into two atomic checks to separate "Definition Fit" from "Context Fit."

Eval 1.1: Core Taxonomy Fit (Sanity Check)

Goal: Ensure the mapped Framework logically contains the diagnosed Skill/Gap. Type: Binary Constraint

{

  "evaluator_name": "rec_framework_taxonomy_fit",

  "type": "binary_constraint",

  "instruction": "Evaluate if the 'skillTag' and 'gapName' belong to the Definition of the selected 'framework'.",

  "reference_definitions": {

    "Cold Calling": {

      "Includes": ["Openers", "Gatekeepers", "Tone", "Hooks", "First 30 seconds"],

      "Excludes": ["Closing", "Negotiation", "Demo", "Deep Discovery"]

    },

    "Discovery": {

      "Includes": ["Questioning", "Pain Extraction", "Active Listening", "Current/Future State"],

      "Excludes": ["Price Negotiation", "Cold Opener", "Final Closing"]

    },

    "Negotiation": {

      "Includes": ["Terms", "Pricing", "Closing Tactics", "Redlines", "Concessions"],

      "Excludes": ["Prospecting", "Qualification", "Agenda Setting"]

    },

    "Objection Handling": {

      "Includes": ["Resistance", "Trust Issues", "Competitor FUD", "Stalls"],

      "Excludes": ["Standard Pricing Discussions", "Routine Info Gathering"]

    }

  },

  "scoring_criteria": {

    "PASS": "Skill/Gap falls within 'Includes' and does NOT violate 'Excludes'.",

    "FAIL": "Skill/Gap violates an 'Excludes' rule (e.g., 'Pricing' mapped to 'Discovery')."

  }

}

Eval 1.2: Evidence-Phase Alignment (Context Check)

Goal: Verify the Evidence supports the Phase implied by the Framework (preventing temporal hallucinations). Type: Negative Constraint

{

  "evaluator_name": "rec_framework_phase_alignment",

  "type": "binary_constraint",

  "instruction": "Check the 'evidence' string for temporal markers that contradict the selected 'framework'.",

  "logic_tree": {

    "framework_cold_calling": {

      "forbidden_terms": ["contract", "renewal", "stakeholders", "legal", "implementation"]

    },

    "framework_negotiation": {

      "forbidden_terms": ["gatekeeper", "who are you", "is this a cold call", "introduction"]

    }

  },

  "scoring_criteria": {

    "PASS": "Evidence does NOT contain forbidden terms for the selected framework.",

    "FAIL": "Evidence suggests a different sales stage than the framework (e.g., 'Cold Calling' framework used but evidence mentions 'contract renewal')."

  }

}

Eval 1.3: Framework Classification Accuracy

Goal: Ensure the AI mapped the specific behavioral gap to the correct Roleplay Framework. Type: Binary Constraint

{

  "evaluator_name": "rec_framework_fit",

  "type": "binary_constraint",

  "instruction": "Evaluate if the selected 'framework' is the correct category for the diagnosed 'gapName' and 'skillTag'.",

  "reference_definitions": {

    "Cold Calling": "Openers, gatekeepers, tone (first 30s).",

    "Discovery": "Questioning, pain extraction, listening.",

    "Negotiation": "Terms, pricing, closing.",

    "Objection Handling": "Resistance before close."

  },

  "scoring_criteria": {

    "PASS": "The Gap (e.g., 'Monologue in Opener') logically falls under the selected Framework (e.g., 'Cold Calling').",

    "FAIL": "Category mismatch (e.g., Mapping 'Closing Technique' to 'Discovery')."

  },

  "output_format": {

    "score": "PASS | FAIL",

    "rationale": "One sentence explaining why the Gap fits or does not fit the Framework definition."

  }

}



Eval 2: Title Style Enforcement

Goal: Enforce the specific [Strong Verb] [Context] template rule. Type: Binary Constraint

{

  "evaluator_name": "rec_title_style",

  "type": "binary_constraint",

  "instruction": "Analyze the 'title' field of the recommendation.",

  "constraint": "Title must start with a present-participle verb (ending in -ing) or strong imperative verb, followed by the context.",

  "scoring_criteria": {

    "PASS": "Title follows pattern (e.g., 'Diffusing the Price Objection', 'Quantifying Business Value').",

    "FAIL": "Title is generic or static (e.g., 'Objection Handling', 'Price Issues')."

  }

}



Eval 3: Insight "You-Phrasing" Check

Goal: Verify the "Why" explanation directly addresses the rep to build motivation. Type: Binary Constraint

{

  "evaluator_name": "rec_insight_voice",

  "type": "binary_constraint",

  "instruction": "Analyze the 'insight' text.",

  "constraint": "Must use second-person phrasing ('You') and reference specific evidence.",

  "scoring_criteria": {

    "PASS": "Text addresses the rep (e.g., 'You missed the upfront contract...') AND is under 140 chars.",

    "FAIL": "Text is third-person/passive (e.g., ' The rep failed to...') OR is too long."

  }

}



Eval 4: Competency Mapping Integrity

Goal: Ensure the engine didn't hallucinate a new competency ID when classifying trends. Type: Binary Constraint

{

  "evaluator_name": "rec_competency_validity",

  "type": "binary_constraint",

  "instruction": "Check the 'metadata.competencyId' against the 'Grounding Competencies' list.",

  "scoring_criteria": {

    "PASS": "The ID exists in the grounding list (or is a valid slug of the Gap Name).",

    "FAIL": "The ID is unrelated to the input data (Hallucination)."

  }

}
